oblem:** The wiki has too many tabs, too much information at once, and it's not immediately clear what to do when you open it.\n\n**What would make it easy for you:**\n\n## 🎯 A Simple Dashboard Design\n\nWhen you open the wiki, you should see THIS:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  🧠 BOBBY'S BRAIN                    [Search 🔍] │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                 │\n│  👋 Welcome back, Bobby                        │\n│  Last conversation: You & YoYo about YouTube   │\n│  [Continue where you left off →]               │\n│                                                 │\n├─────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┤\n│  📊 TODAY       │  🤖 MY TEAM                  │\n│  • 3 new convos │  Dean: Working on wiki      │\n│  • 2 files added│  YoYo: Scripting video      │\n│  • Project: X   │  Rex: Research trending    │\n│                 │                              │\n├─────────────────┼─────────────────────────────┤\n│  📁 QUICK FILES │  🎯 ACTIVE PROJECTS          │\n│  • Screenshots  │  • YouTube channel (active) │\n│  • Projects     │  • TikTok Shop (planning)   │\n│  • Recipes      │  • Content calendar         │\n│                 │                              │\n├─────────────────┴─────────────────────────────┤\n│  📅 RECENT CONVERSATIONS                       │\n│  Dean · 2 hours ago  ·  \"Working on wiki...\"   │\n│  YoYo · 5 hours ago ·  \"Script for video...\"  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**What I propose:**\n\n1. **One-page dashboard** — Everything important on ONE screen, no scrolling needed\n2. **Big buttons** — Don't make you hunt through tabs\n3. **\"Continue where you left off\"** — Shows your last conversation, click to jump back in\n4. **Who's doing what** — See your team at a glance\n5. **Quick access cards** — Screenshots, Projects, Recipes, etc. as big clickable tiles\n6. **Search in the header** — Always visible,